article.description:
Lauren Lueders scored a career-high 14
points to help No. 25 Vanderbilt beat Iowa State 62-53 on Sunday in
the championship game of the Vanderbilt Thanksgiving Tournament.
article.headline: Lueders scores 14 as No. 19 Vanderbilt drops Iowa St.
article.linkText: Lueders' career-high day lifts Vandy over Iowa St.
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Lauren Lueders scored a career-high 14 points to help Vanderbilt (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) beat Iowa State 62-53 on Sunday in the championship game of the Vanderbilt Thanksgiving Tournament.

Tournament MVP Tina Wirth added 10 points and six assists for the Commodores (5-1). Merideth Marsh had 11 points, and Amber Norton finished with 10.

Nicky Wieben had 15 points and nine rebounds for Iowa State (4-1).

The Cyclones outrebounded the Commodores 31-30, including 19-14 in the first half, but committed 18 turnovers.
